
[1]heartily

   HE`ARTILY, adv. [from hearty.] From the heart; with all the heart; with
   sincerity; really.

   I heartily forgive them.

   1. With zeal; actively; vigorously. He heartily assisted the prince.

   2. Eagerly; freely; largely; as, to eat heartily.
